programme.title: Blackhat
programme.desc: After a case of high-level computer hacking arises, a man is released from prison to help American and Chinese authorities pursue a mysterious cyber criminal. The cat-and-mouse chase leads them from the U.S.A to Hong Kong.(n)

programme.title: Lara Croft Tomb Raider: The Cradle Of Life
programme.desc: The British Intelligence recruits archaeologist Lara Croft on a mission to get to Pandora's box, which has the most dangerous disease known to mankind. Evil scientist Jonathan has his sights set on the box as well, and Lara Croft agrees to face him on the condition that the Intelligence release the man she is in a relationship with.(n)

programme.title: Star Wars: Episode VII - The Force Awakens
programme.desc: A seventh installment to the series, with events taking place thirty years after the Battle of Endor and the events portrayed in Return of the Jedi.(n)

programme.title: Rogue One: A Star Wars Story
programme.desc: Before the events of Star Episode IV - A New Hope, and after the founding of the Galactic Empire, a group of rebels planned to carry out a very difficult task, which is to steal the charts of the Star of Death, a deadly weapon with high destructive power, which is owned by the empire.(n)

programme.desc: On the way to the hospital, two paramedics discover that their dying patient has a million dollars sewn into his clothes. Quickly deciding to seize the money after he dies, they soon come to learn that greed always has severe consequences.(n)

programme.title: Backtrace
programme.desc: After a bank heist gone wrong, a thief loses his memory and is put into a prison psychiatric ward. Years later, he's forced to break out of prison and is injected with a drug to help him recover the stolen money.(n)

programme.title: The Hunger Games
programme.desc: In a dystopian post-apocalyptic future in the nation of Panem, Katniss Everdeen (Lawrence) volunteers to take her younger sister's place in the Hunger Games, where boys and girls between the ages of 12 and 18 are required to fight to death in a televised annual event until there is one remaining who will be crowned the victor.(n)

programme.title: Mission: Impossible
programme.desc: After a failed mission leaves him the lone survivor of his team of operatives, Ethan Hunt is accused of betraying his team and must fight to prove his innocence.(n)

programme.title: Nutty Professor II: The Klumps
programme.desc: Scientist Sherman Klump finds his life threatened by his alter ego Buddy Love, who wants to steal his new youth formula and disrupt his marriage plans.(n)

programme.title: Loch Ness
programme.desc: The American scientist Dr. Dempsey, is sent to Scotland on a mission to refute the widespread rumors about the existence of the Loch Ness monster. He's surprised by the hostility of the inhabitants and at the same time he is emotionally attracted to Laura.(n)

programme.title: The Last Boy
programme.desc: With the end of the world getting near, a dying mother decides to send her son to a mysterious and magical world, where all the wishes are granted, and hopes to leave a perfect life for him before she's gone.(n)

programme.title: The Birthday Wish
programme.desc: When Gwen's plans to get engaged on her 30th birthday fall through, she makes a wish to be able to see into the future. But instead of offering answers, her glimpse into the future sends her into a tailspin as it raises questions about whether she is with the right man.(n)

programme.title: Get On Up
programme.desc: A musical biography about the extraordinary life of the Godfather of Soul, James Brown, and how he overcame the challenges of poverty and racism to become one of the most influential musicians of all time.(n)

programme.title: Point Break
programme.desc: Loosely adapted from the 1991 film of the same name, Point Break follows an FBI agent who gets involved with a clan of extreme sports practitioners whom he thinks are behind a series of innovative heists.(n)

programme.title: Collateral
programme.desc: A cab driver is caught in a dangerous game when one of his fares turns out to be a contracted killer who forces him along on his murder spree.(n)

programme.title: Public Enemies
programme.desc: A biopic that chronicles the FBI hunt of the infamous thief John Dillinger and two of his known associates, Baby Face Nelson and Pretty Boy Floyd.(n)

programme.title: The Change Up
programme.desc: A comedy about best friends Mitch and Dave who grow apart as their lives take different paths. When the two simultaneously wish to swap lives, things get complicated as their wish comes true, landing them in the shoes of each other, quite literally.(n)

programme.title: Yours, Mine and Ours

programme.title: Two Weeks
programme.desc: When a North Carolina mother gets diagnosed with end-stage cancer, her four children reunite at her house for a brief, last goodbye, but as death stares their mother in the face, they extend their stay for two weeks and watch movies that cause them to reexamine their relations.(n)

programme.title: Rushmore
programme.desc: 15-year-old Max Fischer attends Rushmore school. He's not doing well in his studies but he loves extracurricular activities, from beekeeping to writing plays, which affects his life.(n)

programme.title: Beauty Shop
programme.desc: Gina decides to open her own hairdresser's shop in Atlanta, which starts to attract customers who seem to care more about talking than getting their hair done.(n)

programme.title: Role Models
